f:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin calculates funding rates hourly using a time-weighted average price (TWAP) mechanism between perpetual and spot prices. The exchange's order book model on Sui enables institutional-grade price discovery with sub-second settlement times. Funding payments are automatically deducted or credited to trader positions at the top of each hour, with rates typically ranging from -0.01% to 0.01% for established DeFi tokens like MKR. Position holders pay or receive funding based on the rate direction and their long/short exposure."}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","MKR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MKR's status as MakerDAO's governance token creates distinct funding rate patterns driven by DeFi protocol developments and governance proposals. The token's mid-tier trading volume on Bluefin generates meaningful arbitrage opportunities without excessive slippage concerns. MKR's correlation with broader DeFi sentiment often leads to predictable funding rate cycles around major protocol updates and regulatory developments."}]]}]
11:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical MKR Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MKR funding rates on Bluefin have shown cyclical patterns correlated with MakerDAO governance cycles and broader DeFi market sentiment. During periods of high governance activity or protocol upgrades, funding rates typically skew positive as traders take long positions anticipating price appreciation. The token's established position in DeFi creates more stable funding patterns compared to newer governance tokens. Seasonal trends emerge around quarterly governance proposals, with rates often turning negative during market downturns when shorts dominate positioning."}]]}]
12:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategy"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin's hourly funding settlements create 24 potential arbitrage windows daily for MKR/USDT, significantly more than traditional 8-hour cycles. Cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities frequently arise between Bluefin and major CEXs due to the Sui ecosystem's relative isolation and different trader behaviors. The 0.02% maker fee structure makes it cost-effective to maintain neutral delta positions while capturing funding rate differentials. Automated strategies can exploit the predictable funding rate resets by positioning ahead of known governance events or correlation breakdowns with ETH."}]]}]
13:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Position Management"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MKR's governance token nature introduces event-driven volatility that can quickly overwhelm funding rate profits, particularly around critical DAO votes or regulatory announcements. Bluefin's relatively low liquidity compared to major CEXs means larger positions may face slippage challenges during rapid unwinding scenarios. The Sui blockchain dependency creates additional technical risks, including potential network congestion during high-activity periods. Traders should maintain strict position sizing limits and implement automated stop-losses to protect against governance-driven price gaps that exceed typical funding rate capture strategies."}]]}]
14:["$","$L16",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are MKR funding rates updated on Bluefin?","answer":"Bluefin updates MKR/USDT funding rates every hour, providing 24 settlement windows daily. This contrasts with most centralized exchanges that use 8-hour funding cycles, creating unique arbitrage timing opportunities for active traders."},{"question":"What makes MKR funding rates different from other DeFi tokens on Bluefin?","answer":"MKR's role as MakerDAO's governance token creates funding patterns tied to protocol governance cycles and DeFi ecosystem health. The token's established market position generates more predictable rate cycles compared to newer governance tokens, while maintaining sufficient volatility for meaningful arbitrage opportunities."},{"question":"Are there minimum position sizes for MKR perpetuals on Bluefin?","answer":"Bluefin typically requires minimum position sizes around $10-50 for MKR perpetuals, making it accessible for smaller arbitrage strategies. However, traders should consider that meaningful funding rate capture often requires larger positions to overcome the 0.02%-0.05% trading fees."},{"question":"How does Bluefin's Sui blockchain integration affect MKR trading costs?","answer":"Sui's low transaction costs keep funding rate settlements inexpensive, typically under $0.01 per position adjustment. The blockchain's fast finality enables near-instant position updates, crucial for timing-sensitive funding rate arbitrage strategies around MakerDAO governance events."}]}]
